official-title.#text: Recognizing the 125th anniversary of the City of Compton.

sponsor.#tail: submitted the following resolution; which was referred to the

committee-name.#text: Committee on Oversight and Government Reform

text.#text:
recognizes and celebrates the City of Compton to the thousands of residents of the city, the county
			 of Los Angeles; and

celebrates the long and exceptional history of the City of Compton and its contributions to
			 California and the United States on the 125th anniversary.
Whereas May 14, 2014, marks the 125th anniversary of incorporation of the City of Compton;

Whereas the City of Compton was the seventh city in the Los Angeles County incorporated on May 14,
			 1888;

quote.#tail: , is the passageway of 25 percent of all United States waterborne international trade;

text.#text:
Whereas the City of Compton has contributed to the diversity of California by electing Douglas
			 Dollarhide, California’s first African-American mayor of a metropolitan
			 city, and Doris Davis, the first African-American woman to be mayor of a
			 major city; and

Whereas the City of Compton has and continues to change and stands poised for success in the years
			 to come: Now, therefore, be it
